lf cringing in the corner of a vast cavern of ice, listening to the howls of Ice-Goblin Sorcerers and quivering with fear at the sound of Ice-Giants storming forward at the other foolish adventurers here with the menace and fury only the truly infernal can muster. Two of my travelling companions (The stalwart Paladin and calm yet deadly Monk) have fled, the third (My longtime travelling companion, the woodelf Druid) having already been slain. I can only hope that whatever Gods the Paladin and Monk prey to have delivered them from here. Myself, I know better than to hope for such a reprieve. My skin burns from the touch of my armour upon my skin, it is so hellishly cold here. My weapons hiss at me, the blood of Goblin-kind crystallizing in a sort of final death-curse. This curious stone figure I found on the body of a slain Goblin-Spellcaster grins at me, and offers none of the usual comforts of treasures gained.. Could this be the thing I so foolishly sought? It seems a rather crude object, for all the hushed whispers it has commanded. My thoughtful reverie is broken by a horrific wail of pain... The Ice-Giant is dead, and the time has come to flee. But there will be a time of reckoning. With a quick nick to my hand, one crimson droplet frozen to the cavern floor seals my word upon this foul place. There will come a time of vengeance. That, at least, brings a tight grin to my face. Stealing down a passageway seemingly undiscovered by the giant lords of this castle gripped by Permanent Frost, sneaking away as a theif and not gloriously emerging as befitting a conqueror... The fate of this place has been sealed indeed, and I count the days until my return. Upon my exit, I find the Paladin alive, he tells me the Monk has wisely chosen to return to Karana. Sindarren, the Woodelf, is also here, having been resurrected by a magnanimous Cleric, and is with the Paladin, nursing memories of the cold chill of Death. These brothers-in-battle of mine shall have their time of vengeance with me, and with that we leave. Cold, beaten, but not broken. No, not beaten while the fire of retribution burns within us.~<br>
<br>
<b>Chromehammer Daemonem</b><br>
